<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3080: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-10T16:00:00-04:00">May 10, 1933—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>39. At diplomatic reception yesterday Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            expressed himself as averse to the Argentine Government taking any
                            further mediatory steps in Chaco dispute at the present time.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>